## Additional Fixes (Post-Review)

### 11. setup_postgresql_databases.sh: Sync MEMPOOL_DB_URL to node.env

**Problem:** When `setup_postgresql_databases.sh` generates a new mempool password, it writes to `aitbc-blockchain-p2p.env` but not `node.env`. The blockchain-node reads `MEMPOOL_DB_URL` from `node.env`, so re-running setup breaks the node with a stale password.

**Fix:** Added logic to update `MEMPOOL_DB_URL` in `node.env` if it exists (sed replace if present, append if missing).

**Files changed:** `scripts/deployment/setup_postgresql_databases.sh`

### 12. Fix p2p_bind_port and network-info Endpoint

**Problem:** `node.env` had `p2p_bind_port=8200` but the actual gossip relay runs on port 7070 (hardcoded in wrapper script). The `/rpc/network-info` endpoint read this and told followers to "Connect via P2P protocol to hub:8200" — wrong port and wrong instructions.

**Fix:**
- Changed `p2p_bind_port` from 8200 to 7070 in `node.env`
- Updated `/rpc/network-info` endpoint to give subscription instructions instead of P2P instructions
- Updated version string to 0.5.4

**Files changed:**
- `/etc/aitbc/node.env`
- `apps/blockchain-node/src/aitbc_chain/rpc/router.py`

### 13. Remove Unused PRIVATE_KEY from node.env

**Problem:** `PRIVATE_KEY` (an Ethereum private key) was in `node.env` but no Python code reads it. Only `GENESIS_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY` is used (by bridge-monitor). Reducing secret surface.

**Fix:** Removed `PRIVATE_KEY` line from `node.env`. Verified bridge-monitor still works (no warnings).

**Files changed:** `/etc/aitbc/node.env`

### 14. Follower Join Flow Verified End-to-End

Tested the complete follower join flow through nginx:
1. `GET /agent/blockchain.env` — downloads clean config with `default_peer_rpc_url`
2. `GET /agent/blockchain-secrets.env` — downloads shared auth secrets
3. `GET /rpc/network-info` — returns correct subscription instructions (port 7070, version 0.5.4)
4. `GET /rpc/head` — follower can read hub block height (30214)
5. `POST /rpc/subscribe` — lease registration works (3600s lease, websocket transport)
6. `POST /rpc/heartbeat` — lease extension works
7. `WS /rpc/subscribe/ws` — WebSocket block push works through nginx (received block)
8. `DELETE /rpc/lease/{node_id}` — lease revocation works
9. `GET /rpc/subscribers` — subscriber list correct

All endpoints verified working through nginx reverse proxy with correct WebSocket upgrade headers.

